to counter negative views about its perceived threat to the united states thomas fingar the oksenberg rohlen distinguished fellow at fsi spoke recently with cctv's world insight about the campaign and about china's soft power strategy noting the link between concern about china and uncertainty about the us economy world insight cctv china's image abroad search aparc search within everything courses events fellowships news op eds people publications research other pages news of interest thomas fingar proposes some questions for the republican presidential debate november 17 2011 cisac fsi stanford shorenstein aparc announcement thomas fingar what does beijing think of us nuclear policy may 27 2011 cisac fsi stanford shorenstein aparc in the news thomas fingar analyzes china and the global system january 4 2011 shorenstein aparc fsi stanford scp news what hu jintao wants to know how the chinese president views the world thomas fingar january 3 2011 foreign policy thomas fingar discusses growth of china's global significance november 17 2010 news thomas fingar debates significance of us field reports from afghanistan released by wikileaks shorenstein aparc cisac in the news france 24 on july 28 2010 support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for international studies encina hall 616 serra st stanford ca 94305 6055 tel 650 723 9741 fax 650 725 2592 mail code 6055
